<%#
  Cosign-rejected modal (audit fix C1) — opened via
  Alpine.store('modals').open('cosign-rejected', {}) when POST
  confirm_onchain_entry returns HTTP 422 with code 'tx_rejected'. The server
  refused to co-sign because the submitted transaction did not match the entry
  it prepared, so the on-chain entry flow stops here.

  Good actors never see this — it only fires on a tampered or mismatched
  transaction. Copy is deliberately reassuring and intentionally vague about
  which server-side check failed (no detail that would help an attacker probe
  the validation). Dismissible; a single 'Got it' button closes the stack
  (escape + click-outside also dismiss via the host).

  Single root element (the host mounts this through its own template x-if;
  sibling roots there silently no-op). No props, so x-data is an empty scope
  whose only job is to give the close button an Alpine tree to reach $store
  from. Keep the x-data body free of double-quotes and backticks — it is a
  double-quoted HTML attribute, so an inner double-quote would close it and
  silently break the modal.
%>
<div x-data="{}">
  <%= render 'modals/blocks/card_header',
        icon_emoji: '🛡️',
        title: 'Transaction not signed' do %>
    For your security we didn't co-sign this transaction — it didn't match the
    entry we prepared, so nothing was submitted and your funds are safe. Please
    close this and try entering again. If it keeps happening,
    <a href="mailto:alex@turfmonster.media" class="text-primary hover:underline">contact support</a>.
  <% end %>
  <button @click="$store.modals.close()"
          class="btn btn-primary btn-lg w-full">Got it</button>
</div>
